## 6. Prompt Templates (Vue + Vuetify + Minimal Churn)

These prompts are written for Cursor and assume MCP tools are available.

### 6.1 Component from a Figma Link (Remote Server)

Use when implementing a single component from a shared Figma node link:

> Implement the UI from this Figma link using **Vue 3 SFC + Vuetify** (no Tailwind).
> Follow our repo conventions and reuse existing components from `src/components/core` and `src/components/base` when possible.  
>  
> Before coding:  
> 1) run `get_design_context` on the exact node,  
> 2) run `get_screenshot` for that node,  
> 3) run `get_variable_defs` and list the variables (names + values) used in this node.  
>  
> Then implement the component in: `src/components/core/<ComponentName>.vue`.  
> Keep changes minimal and align tokens with `src/plugins/vuetify.js` and our existing token helpers.

### 6.2 Multi-Step Flow Planning (No UI Yet)

Use when you have several Figma frames for a single flow and want a plan first:

> We have a multi-step flow across several Figma frames (links provided separately).  
> **Do NOT implement UI yet.**  
>  
> First, propose:  
> - component/view boundaries (one view per step vs shared layout),  
> - routing or stepper state approach,  
> - how tokens and shared components will be reused,  
> - where files will live in the repo (feature folders, core/base components).  
>  
> After we agree on the plan, we will implement step-by-step using `get_design_context` + `get_screenshot` + `get_variable_defs` per frame.

### 6.3 Token-First Analysis (No Components Yet)

Use when you want to align tokens before coding:

> Using the selected Figma node(s), run `get_variable_defs` and produce:  
> 1) a list of color/spacing/typography variables used (names + values); and  
> 2) a suggested mapping to our Vuetify theme tokens in `src/plugins/vuetify.js` and other token sources.  
> Do **not** implement any Vue components yet.

